<%# One fragment of the collaborative document, rendered to ActionText for
    the rest of the app (search, mailers, plain views). The live document
    is already durable; the note is a cache over the store, refreshed on
    read. Loading this page re-renders it server-side when the store has
    changes the note hasn't seen (see NoteMaterializer).

    Reading it is stock ActionText: `note.content` renders through the
    ActionText layout partial and sanitizer like any Rails app. The write
    path is not stock: a conventional rich-text form posts the browser's
    HTML on submit, and a collaborative document can't trust a submitting
    browser. Here the server renders the fragment from its own store. %>
<% if note %>
  <section class="materialized-note" style="margin-top:1rem">
    <h2 style="margin-top:1rem">Materialized ActionText content</h2>
    <p style="color:#666;font-size:.85rem">
      <code>Note#content</code> (an <code>ActionText::RichText</code>),
      rendered by Rails. The server built it from the
      "<%= note.fragment %>" fragment with <code><%= renderer %></code>.
      Refreshed on read; currently through store version
      <%= note.through_version %>. Edit above and reload to see it update.
    </p>
    <div id="saved-note" style="border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:6px;padding:.5rem 1rem">
      <%= note.content %>
    </div>
  </section>
<% end %>
